ens of students and police were injured-and the forced resignation of another Stanford president after just nineteen months in office. Remarkably, Stanford's prestige and academic strength grew unabated throughout this time of crisis. How this came to pass is the central theme of Stanford in Turmoil.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aStudent movementszCaliforniazStanfordxHistoryy20th century. 0aStudent strikeszCaliforniazStanfordxHistoryy20th century. 7aEDUCATION / Higher.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804771016zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804771016423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804771016.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles